author: amunroe
commit_message:
Make the tests compatible with Python 2.6.

Had to rely on unittest2 due to all the new features added in 2.7.  Also had
to work around a wacky bug in 2.6, where a context manager's __exit__ receives
an exception's arguments rather than the exception object, for a few cases of
built-in exceptions.

Only change necessary to pathlib itself was to replace {} with {0} in a couple
format strings.

author: Chris Barnes
commit_message:
Project structure: Refactor into module dirs

Previously, the package and its tests were in single files, which
decreases readability and makes it harder to extend them.

They are now factored into module directories, with changes made as
minimal as possible so that tests work.
